): Endopod 0.25–0.55×exopod length; with appendix interna.

Caridina babaulti
differs from
C. rajadhari
in possessing comparatively shorter rostrum being equal to antennular peduncle or shorter reaching middle of 3 rd antennular peduncle segment (vs. rostrum equal to antennal scale, fractionally longer or shorter reaching the antennular peduncle in
C. rajadhari
); 14–25 teeth proximally leaving 0.1–0.23 of dorsal margin unarmed distally (vs. 26–36 teeth on entire dorsal margin in
C. rajadhari
); 3–7 postorbital teeth which is comparatively in higher range (vs. 3–4 postorbital teeth in
C. rajadhari
); 3–8 teeth proximally on ventral margin with a short unarmed end distally (vs. 8–11 teeth either up to the tip or with a short unarmed end distally in
C. rajadhari
), ca. 25 eggs of 0.50–0.62×0.9–1.0 mm size (vs. ca. 100 eggs of 0.27– 0.35× 0.49–0.60 mm size in
C. rajadhari
).
